frameDefinitions: A physical entity, construed as a point-Sound_source, emits a Sound.
An Agent manipulates a Sound_maker or a Cause causes the Sound_maker to emit a sound.
This frame is concerned with words that describe a person based on a salient part of their body.
This frame contains items which, when manipulated, alter the function of some device, internal or external.
This frame includes words that name medical professionals and is closely related to the Medical_specialties frame.
An Entity is rated as unexpected for its context in terms of its magnitude.
frameExamples: The monks would <t>ring</t> the bell until sundown.
This <t>button</t> makes the radio turn on.
The <t>entire</t> apple was riddled with worms .
listRoleDefinitions: The frame element <fen>Sound_source</fen> is assigned to a constituent referring to a physical entity which emits a sound. Such an entity must have an appropriately complex internal structure such that it can create a sound. For example, a machine or some other thing with moving parts can create sound by itself.

The frame element <fen>Sound</fen> is incorporated in the meaning of the verbs of this frame. Otherwise, this role is assigned to NPs which actually refer to a sound in the presence of the target. This typically occurs when the target is a verb used as a modifier in its <ment>-ing</ment> form, e.g.:
An event in which one or more <fen>Sound_source</fen>s participate and which is accompanied by <fen>Sound</fen>.

The location of the <fen>Sound_source</fen>. This role differs from <fen>Location_of_source</fen> only in terms of point of view; the latter role implies a point of view that is not on the <fen>Sound_source</fen>.
The individual that manipulates a Sound_maker so that it makes Noise.
The entity that produces the Noise, as a result of the action of the Agent.
The inanimate force of nature that causes the <fen>Sound_maker</fen> to produce noise.
The time at which the noise is produced.
The location at which the sound is produced.
This role identifies the <fen>Individual</fen> (or individuals) being described.
This role identifies the <fen>Figure</fen> or form being described by the target.
This role identifies the entity or substance that is designed to have a particular <fen>Use</fen>. This is often an incorporated FE.
The item which is described in terms of its expectedness in the context.
listRoleExamples: It's going to beep again <fex>in two minutes</fex>.
<fex>You</fex> can ring the bell as often as you'd like.
The red-haired <fex>figure</fex> stood in the doorway.
The entire <fex>day</fex> was spent on the project .
